\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
We have studied how extrinsic incentives 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(y\right)$
\end_inset

 affect participation.
 Can providing visibility to contributions 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

 do a better job of encouraging participation?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Yes, but: When we have a homothetic increase in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{a},\mu_{y}$
\end_inset

 this works, but with heterogeneity people may suspect that contributors
 are just doing it to look good: That they are 
\emph on
image-motivated
\emph default
.
 This dampens incentives to participate.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Allow image concerns also to be heterogeneneous:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left(\begin{array}{c}
\mu_{a}\\
\mu_{y}
\end{array}\right)\sim\mathcal{N}\left(\begin{array}{c}
\bar{\mu}_{a}\\
\bar{\mu}_{y}
\end{array},\left[\begin{array}{cc}
\omega_{a}^{2} & \omega_{ay}\\
\omega_{ay} & \omega_{y}^{2}
\end{array}\right]\right),\;\bar{\mu}_{a},\bar{\mu}_{y}\geq0
\]

\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{\mu}$
\end_inset

 are independent.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Benabou & Tirole 2006: Image Rewards
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The first order condition for the choice of 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 is still
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
C^{\prime}\left(a\right)=v_{a}+v_{y}y+r\left(a,y;\boldsymbol{\mu}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Now the reputational concern term in the first order condition 
\begin_inset Formula $r\left(a,y;\boldsymbol{\mu}\right)$
\end_inset

 is also normally distributed, with mean 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{r}\left(a,y;\boldsymbol{\mu}\right)$
\end_inset

 and variance
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\Omega\left(a,y\right)^{2} & \equiv\left(\frac{\partial\mathbb{E}\left[v_{a}\vert a,y\right]}{\partial a}-\frac{\partial\mathbb{E}\left[v_{y}\vert a,y\right]}{\partial a}\right)\\
 & \quad\times\left(\begin{array}{cc}
\omega_{a}^{2} & \omega_{ay}\\
\omega_{ay} & \omega_{y}^{2}
\end{array}\right)\times\left(\begin{array}{c}
\frac{\partial\mathbb{E}\left[v_{a}\vert a,y\right]}{\partial a}\\
-\frac{\partial\mathbb{E}\left[v_{y}\vert a,y\right]}{\partial a}
\end{array}\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Benabou & Tirole 2006: Image Rewards
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Updating still satisfies 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\mathbb{E}\left[v_{a}\vert a,y\right] & =\bar{v}_{a}+\rho\left(a,y\right)\left[ka-\bar{v}_{a}-\bar{v}_{y}y-\bar{r}\left(a,y\right)\right]\\
\mathbb{E}\left[v_{y}\vert a,y\right] & =\bar{v}_{y}+\chi\left(a,y\right)\left[ka-\bar{v}_{a}-\bar{v}_{y}y-\bar{r}\left(a,y\right)\right]
\end{align*}

\end_inset

but now
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\rho\left(a,y\right) & \equiv\frac{\sigma^{2}+y\sigma_{ay}}{\sigma_{a}^{2}+2y\sigma_{ay}+y^{2}\sigma_{y}^{2}+\Omega\left(a,y\right)^{2}}\\
\chi\left(a,y\right) & \equiv\frac{y\sigma^{2}+\sigma_{ay}}{\sigma_{a}^{2}+2y\sigma_{ay}+y^{2}\sigma_{y}^{2}+\Omega\left(a,y\right)^{2}}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Equilibrium solves these differential equations.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
But note they are now nonlinear because of the 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega^{2}$
\end_inset

 term.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Restrict attention to equilibria in the class where 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega\perp a$
\end_inset

.
 This keeps reputations linear in 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Benabou & Tirole 2006: Image Rewards
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\shape smallcaps
proposition 4
\shape default
: (1) 
\emph on
A linear-reputation equilibrium corresponds to a fixed point 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega\left(y\right)$
\end_inset

, solution to
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\Omega\left(y\right)^{2}}{k^{2}}=\omega_{a}^{2}\rho\left(y\right)^{2}-2\omega_{ay}\rho\left(y\right)\chi\left(y\right)+\omega_{y}^{2}\chi\left(y\right)^{2}
\]

\end_inset

The optimal action chosen by an agent with type 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\mathbf{v},\boldsymbol{\mu}\right)$
\end_inset

 is then 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
a=\frac{v_{a}+v_{y}y}{k}+\mu_{a}\rho\left(y\right)-\mu_{y}\chi\left(y\right)
\]

\end_inset

and the marginal reputations are 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial\mathbb{E}\left[v_{a}\vert a,y\right]/\partial a=\rho\left(y\right)k$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial\mathbb{E}\left[v_{y}\vert a,y\right]/\partial a=\chi\left(y\right)k$
\end_inset

, with a net value of 
\begin_inset Formula $r\left(y;\boldsymbol{\mu}\right)=\left[\mu_{a}\rho\left(y\right)-\mu_{y}\chi\left(y\right)\right]k$
\end_inset

 for the agent.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

(2) There always exists such an equilibrium, and if 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{ay}=0$
\end_inset

 it is unique (in the linear reputation class)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Fixed point intuition:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The more variable image motives are, the noisier behavior is as a signal
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{a},v_{y}$
\end_inset

, reducing 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho\left(y\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\chi\left(y\right)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
But the variance is endogenous to behavior which takes into account its
 effect on signal-extraction.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Benabou & Tirole 2006: Image Rewards
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Image rewards give rise to an offsetting 
\emph on
overjustification effect
\emph default
.
 To see this, consider scaling all the reputational weights 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{\mu}=\left(\mu_{a},\mu_{y}\right)$
\end_inset

 up by a prominence factor 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 holding the material incentive 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 constant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Aggregate supply is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\bar{a}\left(y,x\right)=\frac{\bar{v}_{a}+\bar{v}_{y}y}{k}+x\left[\bar{\mu}_{a}\rho\left(y,x\right)-\bar{\mu}\chi\left(y,x\right)\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Increasing 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 has 2 effects:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Direct 
\emph on
amplifying
\emph default
 effect with sign 
\begin_inset Formula $sign\left(\mu_{a}\rho\left(y,x\right)-\mu_{y}\chi\left(y,x\right)\right)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
For socially minded people with 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{a}\gg\mu_{y}$
\end_inset

 this increases incentives to contribute
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
For people worried not to look greedy 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{a}\ll\mu_{y}$
\end_inset

 this decreases incentives.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Indirect 
\emph on
dampening
\emph default
 effect.
 Increasing 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 increases the noise 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $\rightarrow$
\end_inset

 people attribute behavior more to image-seeking 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho\left(y,x\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\chi\left(y,x\right)$
\end_inset

 shrink 
\begin_inset Formula $\rightarrow$
\end_inset

 people respond less to image rewards.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
