\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{1},\pi_{2}$
\end_inset

 are nonpecuniary payoffs: Think of them as non-profits/govt, the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\series bold
Mission-oriented sector
\series default

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Assume 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{1}=\pi_{2}=\hat{\pi}\rightarrow$
\end_inset

 this is a model of horizontal matching: no productivity differences across
 orgs when there is efficient matching.
