\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\shape smallcaps
proposition 1:
\shape default
 
\emph on
Suppose Assumptions 1 and 2 hold.
 An optimal contract 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\left(b_{ij}^{*},w_{ij}^{*}\right)}$
\end_inset

 between a principal of type 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 and an agent of type 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 given a reservation payoff 
\begin_inset Formula $\bar{u}_{j}\in\left[0,\bar{v}_{ij}\right]$
\end_inset

 exists, and has the following features:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
The fixed wage is set at the subsistence level: 
\begin_inset Formula $w_{ij}^{*}=\underline{w}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
The bonus payment is characterized by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
b_{ij}^{*}=\begin{cases}
\max\left\{ 0,\frac{\pi_{i}-\theta_{ij}}{2}\right\}  & \text{if }\bar{u}_{j}\in\left[0,\underline{v}_{ij}\right]\\
\sqrt{2\left(\bar{u}_{j}-\underline{w}\right)}-\theta_{ij} & \text{if }\bar{u}_{j}\in\left[\underline{v}_{ij},\bar{v}_{ij}\right]
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\emph on
The optimal effort level solves: 
\begin_inset Formula $e_{ij}^{*}=b_{ij}^{*}+\theta_{ij}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Besley & Ghatak 2005: Optimal Contracts
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Gives rise to 3 cases
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If the agent is more motivated than the principal and the outside option
 is low, 
\begin_inset Formula $b_{ij}^{*}=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If the principal is more motivated than the agent and the outside option
 is low, 
\begin_inset Formula $b_{ij}^{*}=\tfrac{1}{2}\left(\pi_{i}-\theta_{ij}\right)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If the outside option is high, then 
\begin_inset Formula $b_{ij}^{*}=\sqrt{2\left(\bar{u}_{ij}-\underline{w}\right)}-\theta_{ij}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


