\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Assume that the individuals on the long side of the market gets none of
 the surplus.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
This pins down the outside options.
 For any set of outside options, proposition 1 tells us the optimal contracts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\shape smallcaps
proposition 2
\shape default
: 
\emph on
Consider a matching 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 and associated optimal contracts 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(w_{ij}^{*},b_{ij}^{*}\right)$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $i=0,1,2$
\end_inset

 and 
