\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\shape smallcaps
proposition 3
\shape default
: 
\emph on
Suppose that 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{0}^{a}<n_{0}^{p}$
\end_inset

 (full employment in the profit-oriented sector).
 Then the following matching 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 is stable: 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu\left(a_{j}\right)=p_{j}$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $j=0,1,2$
\end_inset

 and the associated optimal contracts have the following features:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\emph on
(a)
\end_layout

\end_inset


\emph on
The fixed wage is set at the subsistence level, i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $w_{ij}^{*}=\underline{w}$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $j=0,1,2$
\end_inset


