\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Teacher attrition: no significant difference in teacher attrition across
 schools (worried teachers try to select into incentive schools for e.g.)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Student attrition: 7.1% attrition at year 1.
 20.6% at year 2.
 Higher attrition for lower test score children.
 But balanced across treatments.
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
T_{ijkm}\left(Y_{n}\right)=\alpha+\gamma T_{ijkm}\left(Y_{0}\right)+\delta\text{Incentives}+\beta Z_{m}+\varepsilon_{k}+\varepsilon_{jk}+\varepsilon_{ijk}
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{ijkm}$
\end_inset

 is score of student 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 in grade 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 at school 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 in mandal 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{0}$
\end_inset

 denotes baseline tests and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{n}$
\end_inset

indicates test at end of 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 years.
 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{m}$
\end_inset

 are mandal dummies
\end_layout

