\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Duflo et al.
 2012: Estimation
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Extend the above in 2 ways
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Incorporate observables into 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

.
 Use attendance in control group in same geographic block and teacher's
 score on the admission exam to shift 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Relax assumption that the outside option is the same for everyone.
 Estimate fixed effects 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{i}$
\end_inset

 or random coefficients 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{im}$
\end_inset

 drawn from normal distribution or from a mixture of two normally distributed
 types.
\end_layout

