\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Run treatment regressions of scores in mid- and end-term exams.
 Test scores are highly autocorrelated so gain lots of precision by controlling
 for pre-scores.
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
Score_{ijk} & =\beta_{1}+\beta_{2}Treat_{j}+\beta_{3}Pre\_Writ_{ij}+\beta_{r}Oral\_Score_{ij}\\
 & \quad+\beta_{5}Written\_Score_{ij}+\varepsilon_{ijk}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $Pre\_Writ_{ij}$
\end_inset

 is a dummy for taking the written test at baseline (they did either the
 written or oral test), 
\begin_inset Formula $Oral\_Score_{ij}$
\end_inset

 is the score on the oral exam (or 0 if did the written exam) and 
\begin_inset Formula $Written\_Score_{ij}$
\end_inset

 is the score on the written exam (or 0 if did the oral exam).
\end_layout

