Truth-telling by Third-party Auditors and the Response of Polluting Firms:
 Experimental Evidence from India
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Duflo et al 2013: Introduction
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Third-party audits are a common mechanism to monitor compliance with regulations
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
financial accounting of firms
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
food safety, health care, flowers etc in consumer & commodity markets
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
environmental regulation
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Usually, the auditor is chosen by, pair by, and reports to the audited firm.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Creates a conflict of interest: Report the truth or report what is beneficial
 for your client?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Conduct an experiment in India to investigate whether this can be overcome.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Duflo et al 2013: Setting
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Study conducted in Gujarat: 5% of India's population but 9% of manufacturing
 employment and 19% of output
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
3 of the 5 most polluted rivers in India are in Gujarat.
 Air pollution dangerous for human health in the cities.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Gujarat Pollution Control Board (GPCB) has a stringent regulatory framework
 for pollution control.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
2 Main instruments to enforce regulations
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Inspections (Duflo et al 2018 next week)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
third-party environmental audits.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
